id: pmc-yzho
title: Detect missing git tag history before release-window changelog checks
description: "Commands using --since-previous-tag or --until-release-tag silently fall back to an incomplete window when a shallow or sandboxed checkout omits tag refs, then misreport a correct CHANGELOG.md as stale."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: changelog,git-tags,release-gate,shallow-clone,ux
created_at: "2026-07-13T23:08:49.280Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T11:43:35.974Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-18T10:21:24.702Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "When tag-derived flags are requested and required refs are unavailable, the CLI emits a structured actionable diagnostic that identifies missing git tag history instead of reporting CHANGELOG.md stale; Full-tag behavior and generated bytes remain unchanged; Automated tests cover shallow/tagless and full-tag repositories; Release documentation gives the recovery command"
definition_of_ready: Confirm current tag resolution behavior and supported shallow-clone contract; preserve existing output compatibility when tags exist.
reviewer: greptile
risk: medium
confidence: high
sprint: 2026-07-production
release: next
reporter: codex-root
severity: medium
environment: Depth-1 no-tags clone of PR 67 with Node 22.19.0 npm 11.17.0 and pm CLI 2026.7.13
repro_steps: "Clone the repository with --depth 1 --no-tags, run NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG=/dev/null npm ci, then run NPM_CONFIG_USERCONFIG=/dev/null npm run release:check; the final changelog check reports out of date although the same commit passes with tag history."
expected_result: Tag-derived changelog validation fails with a precise missing-tag-history diagnostic and a git fetch recovery command.
actual_result: The CLI treats unavailable release tags as an unbounded window and reports CHANGELOG.md out of date.
affected_version: 2026.7.13
component: src/release-context.ts
regression: false
customer_impact: Prevents agents and review sandboxes from wasting time regenerating a correct changelog or committing incorrect release content.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T23:08:49.280Z",codex-root,Discovered from Greptile PR 67 P1 and reproduced independently in a clean depth-1 no-tags clone.
  "2026-07-18T11:43:35.972Z",pi-agent,"Greptile CLI P2 (recoveryCommands compound-entry): split the two --no-tags recovery arrays into discrete independently-executable entries; message text unchanged; JSDoc clarified; tests updated (generator.test.ts 1377/1426), message-match assertion preserved. Build+tests green, CHANGELOG regenerated."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T10:19:25.295Z",pi-agent,"Root cause: resolveReleaseContext/resolveReleaseTagWindows silently fell back to an unbounded/incomplete window when shallow checkouts omitted tag refs. Fix: assertReleaseTagHistory guard in src/release-context.ts fails fast with structured E_MISSING_TAG_HISTORY diagnostic (MissingTagHistoryError, code + recoveryCommands git fetch --tags --unshallow / git fetch --tags) before any tag-derived window resolution. Only shallow checkouts (git rev-parse --is-shallow-repository=true) error; zero-tag full clones keep intentional first-release fallbacks (unbounded --since, pending-version windows)."
  "2026-07-18T10:19:25.898Z",pi-agent,"Wired through all entry points: CLI (main error handler, exit 1), pm extension changelog generate + changelog export (wrapped as PmCliError EXIT_CODE.GENERIC_FAILURE=1). Byte-identical proof with full tags: changelog:full output and --since-previous-tag/--until-release-tag stdout path both unchanged vs HEAD dist. Tests: 6 new (shallow tagless, shallow with tip tag, full clone, zero-tag first-release, CLI end-to-end incl. recovery via git fetch --tags --unshallow, extension PmCliError) — 148 total pass."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T23:08:49.280Z",codex-root,A changelog derived from git release windows cannot be validated from a checkout that omits those refs; missing context must be diagnosed separately from stale output.
