  docs/usage.md,project,null
  README.md,project,null
close_reason: "Tag-derived flags (--since-previous-tag/--until-release-tag/--all-release-tags) now fail fast with structured E_MISSING_TAG_HISTORY diagnostic (MissingTagHistoryError: stable code + recovery commands git fetch --tags --unshallow / git fetch --tags) when the checkout is shallow, instead of silently deriving an incomplete window and misreporting CHANGELOG.md as stale. CLI exits 1 via main error handler; extension surfaces PmCliError exitCode=1. Zero-tag full clones keep intentional first-release fallbacks. Byte-identical proof with full tags: changelog:full output and tag-flags stdout path unchanged vs HEAD dist (15719 bytes). 6 new tests cover shallow/tagless, shallow-with-tip-tag, full-clone, zero-tag first-release, CLI end-to-end with recovery, and extension error; npm test 148/148 pass. docs/release.md, docs/usage.md, README.md document the prerequisite and recovery."
body: "## Context\\n\\nProject management is context management: release-window validation must distinguish stale generated content from missing git context. Greptile reproduced the ambiguity in a tagless PR sandbox; a local depth-1/no-tags clone reproduced the same final-gate failure while full-history local and GitHub CI checks pass.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\nAdd explicit release-tag prerequisite diagnostics without weakening full-history changelog validation."
